    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - REMOVE - AUXILIARY SECTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>AUXILIARY SECTION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Break loose the retaining bolts in the auxiliary housing flange (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302123">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302123" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302123" filename="../figg13/g1302123.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Loosen Retaining Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four bolts from the countershaft rear bearing cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302124">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302124" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302124" filename="../figg13/g1302124.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 24. Countershaft Rear Bearing Cover</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear countershaft bearing cover and countershaft shim (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302125">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302125" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302125" filename="../figg13/g1302125.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 25. Remove Cover &#38; Shim</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Auxiliary countershaft shim gauge or retaining straps must be installed to prevent
                        countershafts from falling free of auxiliary housing.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Do not use an air gun. Tighten by hand until the bolts are snug.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the shim gauge on each countershaft with two 3/8 inch x 1 inch bolts and one 3/8
                inch &#215; 2-1/2 inch through the center hole (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302126">left, Figure 26</hotlnk>). Remove the retaining bolts around the auxiliary
                housing rear flange (right).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302126" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302126" filename="../figg13/g1302126.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 26. Remove Retaining Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the auxiliary section from the main case and clean both gasket surfaces (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302127">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302127" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302127" filename="../figg13/g1302127.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 27. Clean Gasket Surfaces</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Three tapped holes are located in the housing flange to separate the auxiliary section from
                        the main case.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>This procedure can be performed in both the horizontal and vertical positions.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
